(ruyi-task
  (goal "Add unit tests for the under-tested core modules: (1) engine.rkt — test execute-one-iteration logic including soft max-diff limit behavior (revise when diff exceeds limit with attempts remaining, discard when attempts exhausted), and iteration result handling; (2) review.rkt — test review prompt construction and score/feedback parsing from reviewer output; (3) claude.rkt — test argument building for claude-agent and claude-execute calls, and any other exported pure functions beyond plan-says-skip?. Use mocks to isolate from real Claude API and git side effects.")
  (judgement "1. All tests pass: raco test tests/ exits cleanly with no failures. 2. Existing tests remain green — no regressions. 3. engine.rkt tests cover at least 3 distinct behaviors of execute-one-iteration (e.g. success path, revise-on-high-diff, discard-when-exhausted). 4. review.rkt tests cover prompt construction and score parsing for at least 3 scenarios (pass, fail, edge cases like missing score). 5. claude.rkt tests cover argument construction for at least 2 exported functions. 6. All tests use mocks/stubs for external calls (Claude CLI, git, shell) — no real subprocess invocations. 7. No trivially-true tests (every test must be falsifiable by a plausible bug).")
  (max-revisions 3)
  (min-score 8))
